name: 2014 Dupont Research
tagline: Data and Analysis Materials in Research for Dr. Brandon Dupont (WWU Department of Economics)
body:
## Updates > Update: 06/13/2014 > - Creation of repository > - Automatic .gitattributes from GitHub > - ICPSR 2896 CSV Files for DS 7-25 and 43 > - ICPSR 2896 DTA (Stata) Files for DS 7-25 and 43 > - ICPSR 2896 Codebook > - ICPSR 2896 Description > - ICPSR 2896 Manifest > - ICPSR 2896 Related Literature > - ICPSR 2896 Series 180 Related Literature > - ICPSR 2896 Terms of Use > - ICPSR 2896 Table of Contents for DS 7-25 and 43 > - ICPSR 2896 Dataset Summary for DS 7-25 and 43 ## Citations ### ICPSR 2896 Currently in use: - ICPSR 2896 Datasets 7-25 - ICPSR 2896 Dataset 43 All data listed as ICPSR 2896 are from *Historical, Demographic, Economic, and Social Data: The United States, 1790-2002*. Principal is Michael R. Haines, Colgate University, Interuniversity Consortium for Political and Social Research. Persistent and stable access: http://doi.org/10.3886/ICPSR02896.v3 > Haines, Michael R., and Inter-university Consortium for Political and Social Research. Historical, Demographic, Economic, and Social Data: The United States, 1790-2002. ICPSR02896-v3. Ann Arbor, MI: Inter-university Consortium for Political and Social Research [distributor], 2010-05-21. http://doi.org/10.3886/ICPSR02896.v3 **DO NOT USE ANY ICPSR DATA OR DATASETS WITHOUT AUTHORIZED PERMISSION FROM ICPSR** ### Authors and Contributors Dr. Brandon Dupont, Associate Professor of Economics, Western Washington University: principle investigator and lead researcher.
Jade Coppieters @jadecoppieters: assisting with data processing, research, and analysis.
